article.description: — Matai Baptiste's 12 points helped Boston University defeat Sacred Heart 70-49 on Saturday.
article.headline: Baptiste scores 12 in Boston University's 70-49 victory over Sacred Heart
article.linkText: Baptiste scores 12 in Boston University's 70-49 victory over Sacred Heart
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. -- — Matai Baptiste's 12 points helped Boston University defeat Sacred Heart 70-49 on Saturday. Baptiste shot 5 for 9, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc for the Terriers (3-5,). Otto Landrum shot 2 of 7 from the field and 5 for 5 from the line to add nine points. Ethan Okwuosa had nine points and was 2 of 8 shooting, including 1 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line. Nico Galette finished with 13 points, six rebounds and three steals for the Pioneers (4-5). Aidan Carpenter added 12 points and two blocks for Sacred Heart. Alex Sobel also had 10 points, six rebounds and two blocks. NEXT UP Both teams play on Wednesday. Boston University hosts Maine and Sacred Heart travels to play St. John's. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
